cs.DC, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.IT, cs.LG 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper deals with distributed network-wide averaging and proposes a new gossip algorithm for the same. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also a likely category as the paper deals with communication paths and their selection for efficient averaging. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper deals with convergence speed and performance analysis of the proposed algorithm. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is a possible category as the paper may involve information theoretic concepts in the analysis of the algorithm. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possible category as gossip algorithms are often used in distributed machine learning settings for averaging and consensus.
